    "Lectures by <a href=\"/lowye\">Emanuel L\u00f6wy</a> during study at the University of Rome around 1896 convinced her to study classical art.": [],
    "Richter was admitted to Girton College, Cambridge University, in 1901 where her don, Katherine Jex-Blake (1860-1951), along with <a href=\"/stronges\">Eug\u00e9nie Sellers Strong</a>, was the translator of elder Piny's passages on the history of art.": [
